radiographic_examinations.findings: Postoperative changes from the T7 level to the T10 level, with no evidence of any abnormal masses. A central syrinx, 1 to 2 mm in diameter, extended over a length of 2 cm at the T9 level.

radiographic_examinations.date: Eight months after the previous MRI
radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild disk bulges, without disk herniation, a mass, or nerve-root impingement. Evidence of a prior partial laminectomy at the L4 and L5 levels.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: MRI examination of the cervical spine
radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild spondylosis at multiple levels; thickening of the ligamentum flavum, which caused mild spinal stenosis but no deformity of the spinal cord.
Scattered perivascular mononuclear infiltrates; axonal swellings in some fibers consistent with early degeneration.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Eleven months later, revealed a 61% reduction in axonal density, to 189 neurites per square millimeter, significantly below normal for her age.
